revision.text:
{{High-use}}

This template will automatically categorize redirects into their appropriate rcat protection category.

== Usage ==
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">
#REDIRECT [[(redirect target)]]

{{R protected}}
</syntaxhighlight>

This template is also called automatically by {{t|redirect category shell}}; if that template is used on the page, this template does not need to be included in the redirect cat templates as it will be called directly. A protected page also using {{t|r from move}} would look like this:

<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">
#REDIRECT [[(redirect target)]]

{{Redirect category shell|1=
{{R from move}}
}}
</syntaxhighlight>

For another example of this use case, see [[Wikipedia:Example of a broken redirect]].

== Examples ==
Fully protected: {{R protected|protlevel=sysop|nocat=true}}
Template protected: {{R protected|protlevel=templateeditor|nocat=true}}
Extended protected: {{R protected|protlevel=extendedconfirmed|nocat=true}}
Semi protected: {{R protected|protlevel=autoconfirmed|nocat=true}}

==Subpages==
* [[Template:R protected/full|/full]]
* [[Template:R protected/template|/template]]
* [[Template:R protected/excon|/excon]]
* [[Template:R protected/semi|/semi]]

<includeonly>{{Sandbox other||
<!-- Categories go below this line -->
[[Category:Redirect templates|Protected]]
[[Category:Protection templates]]
[[Category:Unknown namespace redirect templates]]

}}</includeonly>
